  "title": "QS cum Drafter #81953",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><ul><li>Industry/ Organization Type: Civil Engineer Contractor</li><li>Position Title: <strong>QS cum Drafter</strong></li><li>Working Location: Tuas</li><li>Working Hours: 5-days (Mon-Fri: 8.30am-6pm)</li><li>Salary Package: <strong>Basic up to $4,000 + Bonus</strong></li><li>Duration: Permanent</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Familiar with standard contracts and tender documents.</li><li>Join site visits with the Project Manager and/or management team.</li><li>Prepare tender submissions or cost estimates based on instructions given.</li><li>Work with clients on Bills of Quantities and cost submissions.</li><li>Source materials and liaise with suppliers and vendors to request and review quotations.</li><li>Review market unit rates regularly to keep material pricing updated.</li><li>Coordinate with suppliers/sub-contractors on products/services and follow up on Bills of Quantities matters.</li><li>Ensure contract and purchasing activities follow workplace safety and relevant construction requirements.</li><li>Prepare structural shop drawings and as-built drawings using AutoCAD.</li><li>Track daily/weekly work progress and report updates to the Project Manager.</li><li>Handle progress claims, variation orders, and final accounts.</li><li>Perform other duties assigned by the Project Manager to support project needs.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>APPLY NOW!!!</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor’s Degree / Diploma in Civil & Structural Engineering.</li><li>Proficient in MS Office and AutoCAD.</li><li>Good communication skills and able to work well with different stakeholders.</li><li>Organised, detail-oriented, and demonstrates a positive work attitude.</li><li></li></ul><p>Kindly apply through <strong>ANY </strong>of the following methods:</p><ul><li>Submit your application by clicking the <strong>APPLY </strong>button;</li><li>Email your resume to <a href=\"mailto:Job@anradus.com.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Job@anradus.com.sg</a>. Please indicate <strong>#81953 </strong>on the email subject.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Anradus Application Policy:</strong> We value each application and ensure every resume is reviewed. Our process is efficient, typically concluding within <strong>3 working days</strong>. If you do not receive communication from us within this timeframe, it's likely that your application has not been shortlisted by our client. In such cases, we recommend continuing your job search to maximize your opportunities.</p><p><br /><br /></p><p>Anradus Pte Ltd | EA License No. 20C0161 | Rachael Lee | EA Reg No.: R2093131</p>",
